@startuml
title Justice40 Tool - Data Flow Sequence Diagram

actor User
participant "CLI\n(application.py)" as CLI
participant "Runner\n(runner.py)" as Runner
participant "ETL Classes\n(base.py)" as ETL
participant "DataSource\n(datasource.py)" as DataSource
participant "External APIs\n(Census, FEMA, EPA)" as APIs
participant "S3 Data Lake" as S3
participant "Score Runner\n(score_runner.py)" as ScoreRunner
participant "Scoring Engine\n(ScoreA, ScoreB, etc.)" as Scoring
participant "Tile Generator\n(generate.py)" as TileGen
participant "Tippecanoe" as Tippecanoe
participant "Client App\n(React/Gatsby)" as Client
participant "Map Component\n(J40Map.tsx)" as Map

== Data Pipeline - ETL Process ==

User -> CLI: Execute ETL command
activate CLI
CLI -> Runner: Orchestrate ETL execution
activate Runner

Runner -> ETL: Initialize ETL class
activate ETL

ETL -> DataSource: Request data retrieval
activate DataSource

DataSource -> APIs: Fetch data from external sources
activate APIs
APIs --> DataSource: Return raw data
deactivate APIs

DataSource -> DataSource: Handle file/ZIP extraction
DataSource --> ETL: Provide extracted data
deactivate DataSource

ETL -> ETL: Transform data\n(clean, validate, normalize)
ETL -> ETL: Validate data integrity\n(missing values, duplicates)

ETL -> S3: Store processed data
activate S3
S3 --> ETL: Confirm storage
deactivate S3

ETL --> Runner: ETL complete
deactivate ETL

Runner -> Runner: Process concurrent ETLs\n(high-memory support)
Runner --> CLI: All ETLs complete
deactivate Runner

== Scoring Process ==

CLI -> ScoreRunner: Execute scoring command
activate ScoreRunner

ScoreRunner -> S3: Retrieve processed data
activate S3
S3 --> ScoreRunner: Return data
deactivate S3

ScoreRunner -> Scoring: Calculate Justice40 scores
activate Scoring

Scoring -> Scoring: Apply thresholds and criteria
Scoring -> Scoring: Identify disadvantaged communities
Scoring -> Scoring: Generate multiple score methodologies

Scoring --> ScoreRunner: Return calculated scores
deactivate Scoring

ScoreRunner -> S3: Store score results
activate S3
S3 --> ScoreRunner: Confirm storage
deactivate S3

ScoreRunner --> CLI: Scoring complete
deactivate ScoreRunner

== Map Tile Generation ==

CLI -> TileGen: Generate map tiles
activate TileGen

TileGen -> S3: Retrieve GeoJSON data
activate S3
S3 --> TileGen: Return GeoJSON
deactivate S3

TileGen -> Tippecanoe: Process tiles at various zoom levels
activate Tippecanoe
Tippecanoe -> Tippecanoe: Generate tile pyramid
Tippecanoe -> Tippecanoe: Include tribal land areas
Tippecanoe --> TileGen: Return generated tiles
deactivate Tippecanoe

TileGen -> S3: Store map tiles
activate S3
S3 --> TileGen: Confirm storage
deactivate S3

TileGen --> CLI: Tile generation complete
deactivate TileGen

CLI --> User: Pipeline execution complete
deactivate CLI

== Client-Side Data Visualization ==

User -> Client: Access CEJST website
activate Client

Client -> Client: Initialize React app\n(Gatsby build)

Client -> S3: Request map tiles
activate S3
S3 --> Client: Return tiles
deactivate S3

Client -> S3: Request score data
activate S3
S3 --> Client: Return scores
deactivate S3

Client -> Map: Render map with data
activate Map

Map -> Map: Load MapLibre GL
Map -> Map: Display tiles at appropriate zoom
Map -> Map: Apply feature flags

Map --> Client: Map rendered
deactivate Map

Client -> Client: Display AreaDetail components\n(Indicators, Categories)

Client --> User: Show interactive visualization
deactivate Client

User -> Client: Interact with map\n(zoom, select area)
activate Client

Client -> Map: Update view
activate Map
Map -> S3: Request additional data
activate S3
S3 --> Map: Return detailed area data
deactivate S3
Map --> Client: Update display
deactivate Map

Client --> User: Show updated information
deactivate Client

@enduml
